  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 22 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Tungsten has a resistivity of \\(5.6 \\times 10^{-8} \\ \\Omega \\cdot \\text{m}\\). What is the resistance of a \\(1.2 \\ \\text{m}\\) long tungsten wire with a radius of \\(1.0 \\times 10^{-3} \\ \\text{m}\\)?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "\\(0.30 \\Omega\\)",
        "\\(0.021 \\Omega\\)",
        "\\(0.05 \\Omega\\)",
        "\\(0.001 \\Omega\\)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\(0.021 \\Omega\\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>The resistance \\( R \\) of a wire is calculated using the formula:</p> \\[ R = \\frac{\\rho L}{A} \\] <p>Where:<br> • \\( \\rho \\) (resistivity of tungsten) = \\( 5.6 \\times 10^{-8} \\ \\Omega \\cdot \\text{m} \\),<br> • \\( L \\) (length) = \\( 1.2 \\ \\text{m} \\),<br> • \\( r \\) (radius) = \\( 1.0 \\times 10^{-3} \\ \\text{m} \\),<br> • \\( A \\) (cross-sectional area) = \\( \\pi r^2 = \\pi \\times (1.0 \\times 10^{-3})^2 = 3.14 \\times 10^{-6} \\ \\text{m}^2 \\).</p> <p>Substituting the values:</p> \\[ R = \\frac{(5.6 \\times 10^{-8}) (1.2)}{3.14 \\times 10^{-6}} \\] \\[ R = \\frac{6.72 \\times 10^{-8}}{3.14 \\times 10^{-6}} \\] \\[ R \\approx 0.0214 \\ \\Omega \\] <p>Rounded to two significant figures, the resistance is <b>\\( 0.021 \\ \\Omega \\)</b>.</p> <p>Note: The resistivity of tungsten is correctly given as \\( 5.6 \\times 10^{-8} \\ \\Omega \\cdot \\text{m} \\), and the radius is in meters (not ohms).</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
